<paragraph blockId="6.[140,1161,1558,1674]" lastBlockId="7.[140,1160,177,570]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="36" pageId="6" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[179,237,1558,1582]" pageId="6" pageNumber="35">Male</emphasis>
. Frons as 
<figureCitation box="[345,423,1558,1582]" captionStart="Figs 24–27" captionStartId="5.[140,177,1622,1641]" captionTargetBox="[146,1152,642,1592]" captionTargetId="figure-173@5.[619,1152,934,1591]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 24–27. Megaselia hortenensis n. sp., male. 24 – frons; 25 – postpedicels, palps and proboscis; 26 – postpedicel; 27 – mesopleuron and notopleuron;" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252447" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6252447/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="35">Fig. 24</figureCitation>
, with dense but very fine microtrichia. Cheek with 3 bristles and jowl with 3 that are longer and more robust. Postpedicels (
<figureCitation box="[717,798,1589,1613]" captionStart="Figs 24–27" captionStartId="5.[140,177,1622,1641]" captionTargetBox="[146,1152,642,1592]" captionTargetId="figure-173@5.[619,1152,934,1591]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 24–27. Megaselia hortenensis n. sp., male. 24 – frons; 25 – postpedicels, palps and proboscis; 26 – postpedicel; 27 – mesopleuron and notopleuron;" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252447" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6252447/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="35">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
), without SPS vesicles, palps and proboscis as 
<figureCitation box="[283,364,1619,1643]" captionStart="Figs 24–27" captionStartId="5.[140,177,1622,1641]" captionTargetBox="[146,1152,642,1592]" captionTargetId="figure-173@5.[619,1152,934,1591]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 24–27. Megaselia hortenensis n. sp., male. 24 – frons; 25 – postpedicels, palps and proboscis; 26 – postpedicel; 27 – mesopleuron and notopleuron;" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252447" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6252447/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="35">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
, the labella with only a few short spinules below. Thorax brown. Three notopleural bristles with no cleft in front of these mesopleuron with only 3 small hairs 
<figureCitation box="[1077,1157,1650,1674]" captionStart="Figs 24–27" captionStartId="5.[140,177,1622,1641]" captionTargetBox="[146,1152,642,1592]" captionTargetId="figure-173@5.[619,1152,934,1591]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 24–27. Megaselia hortenensis n. sp., male. 24 – frons; 25 – postpedicels, palps and proboscis; 26 – postpedicel; 27 – mesopleuron and notopleuron;" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252447" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6252447/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="35">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
. 
<pageTitle box="[140,1160,177,201]" pageId="7" pageNumber="36">Scutellum (Fig. 28) with an anterior pair of small hairs and a posterior pair of bristles. Abdominal</pageTitle>
tergites brown as Fig. Hypopygium as 
<figureCitation box="[577,704,208,232]" captionStart="Figs 28–35" captionStartId="6.[140,177,1483,1502]" captionTargetBox="[146,1158,171,1453]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs 28–35. Megaselia hortenensis n. sp., male. 28 –scutellum; 29 – abdomen; 30 – left face of hypopygium; 31 – left face of hypandrium and penis complex; 32 – right face of hypopygium; 33 – front tarsus; 34 – hind leg; 35 – wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252451" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6252451/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="36">Figs 30–32</figureCitation>
. Legs dusky yellow to paler. Fore tarsus (
<figureCitation box="[147,225,239,263]" captionStart="Figs 28–35" captionStartId="6.[140,177,1483,1502]" captionTargetBox="[146,1158,171,1453]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs 28–35. Megaselia hortenensis n. sp., male. 28 –scutellum; 29 – abdomen; 30 – left face of hypopygium; 31 – left face of hypandrium and penis complex; 32 – right face of hypopygium; 33 – front tarsus; 34 – hind leg; 35 – wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252451" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6252451/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="36">Fig. 33</figureCitation>
) with posterodorsal hair palisade on segments 1–4 and 5 clearly longer than 4. Dorsal hair palisade of mid tibia extends about 0.62–0.63 its length. Hind leg as 
<figureCitation box="[911,988,269,293]" captionStart="Figs 28–35" captionStartId="6.[140,177,1483,1502]" captionTargetBox="[146,1158,171,1453]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs 28–35. Megaselia hortenensis n. sp., male. 28 –scutellum; 29 – abdomen; 30 – left face of hypopygium; 31 – left face of hypandrium and penis complex; 32 – right face of hypopygium; 33 – front tarsus; 34 – hind leg; 35 – wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252451" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6252451/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="36">Fig. 34</figureCitation>
, the hairs below the basal half of the femur being shorter than those of anteroventral row of outer half. Hind tibia with about 20 weakly differentiated posterodorsal hairs, without anterodorsals, and spinules of apical combs simple. Wings (
<figureCitation box="[456,532,361,385]" captionStart="Figs 28–35" captionStartId="6.[140,177,1483,1502]" captionTargetBox="[146,1158,171,1453]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs 28–35. Megaselia hortenensis n. sp., male. 28 –scutellum; 29 – abdomen; 30 – left face of hypopygium; 31 – left face of hypandrium and penis complex; 32 – right face of hypopygium; 33 – front tarsus; 34 – hind leg; 35 – wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252451" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6252451/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="36">Fig. 35</figureCitation>
) 
<quantity box="[540,697,361,385]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1349999999999998" metricValueMax="1.14" metricValueMin="1.13" pageId="7" pageNumber="36" unit="mm" value="1.1349999999999998" valueMax="1.14" valueMin="1.13">1.13–1.14 mm</quantity>
long. Costal index 0.39–0.42. Costal ratios 3.25–4.58: 1.08–1.54: 1. Costal cilia (of section 3) 
<quantity box="[721,805,392,416]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="36" unit="mm" value="0.7">0.7 mm</quantity>
long. No vein 3 hair. 2 unequal axillary bristles, the outermost being 
<quantity box="[536,692,423,447]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" metricValueMax="9.0" metricValueMin="7" pageId="7" pageNumber="36" unit="mm" value="0.08" valueMax="0.09" valueMin="0.07">0.07–0.09 mm</quantity>
long. Haltere brown.
</paragraph>
